A man has been arrested after class A drugs with a street value of &pound;700,000 were seized in central Glasgow.
Police acting under warrant searched a flat in the city's St Mungo's Place, just behind Cathedral Street, at about 19:15 on Wednesday.
Officers recovered heroin believed to be worth about &pound;665,000 and cocaine worth about &pound;35,000. 
The 48-year-old man who was arrested is expected to appear from police custody at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Friday.
